description:
I found a script that can turn Gutenberg HTML files into well-formed BBeB (.lrf) files suitable for the Sony PRS-500 and PRS-505 reader devices (and hopefully retaining the images and chapter bookmarks). So I automated it to pull in all the books I could, cleaned them up a little, removed the magazines, and added a sprinkling of Creative Commons SF authors, and here we are. Some 7.5 Gb of books.

Since this was an automated process I am sure there are mistakes, omissions, and malformatted files, but the files I have spot-checked looked fine. It also didn&amp;#039;t cost me a lot of time :)
